#  Fake News Detection
This project is focused on identifying whether a news article is FAKE or REAL using machine learning and natural language processing (NLP). It utilizes the Fake and Real News Dataset from Kaggle and covers a complete ML pipeline â€” from data cleaning to web deployment.
# Colab Link https://colab.research.google.com/drive/1FuFkNeoZ06w2Atu3LSAtBC-syuR_K8Eb#scrollTo=dqVuMWUvyZGu

# Project Summary
Cleaned and merged real/fake news data

Used NLP techniques: tokenization, stopword removal, and TF-IDF vectorization

Trained ML models like Logistic Regression and SVM

Evaluated using metrics: Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1-score, ROC-AUC

Visualized results with confusion matrix and ROC curve

Deployed an interactive web app using Streamlit

# Technologies Used
Python

Scikit-learn

Pandas & NumPy

Matplotlib & Seaborn

Streamlit

TfidfVectorizer

Logistic Regression / SVM

# Deliverables
.py script with clean modular code

Visualizations for model evaluation

Web app (Streamlit) to classify new articles

PDF/Markdown project report (methodology, results, insights)
